Ten bandits terrorizing communities in Numan area of Adamawa state have been killed by troops conducting clearance operations in the area. Director Army Public Relations, Texas Chukwu in a statement said one of the bandits, Adamu Umar was also captured during the operation. “Items recovered include: 18 motorcycles, two Dane guns, one sub machine gun, one double barrel,fFour cartridges, thirteen rounds of 7.62mm ammunition NATO special, and one cutlass. “Also, one of the bandits, Adamu Umar was captured during the operation. ” Preliminary investigation is ongoing; meanwhile, the suspects and the remains of the 10 bandits neutralized have been handed over to the Nigeria Police. The army advised the general public to always report any suspicious activities to the law enforcement agents for prompt action.    Follow us on twitter @NigeriaTodayNG Also, Like us on facebook